Clone esp-idf: 
- mkdir -p $HOME/git
- git -C $HOME/git clone https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf.git


Setup install:
- cd ~/esp/esp-idf
- ./install.sh
- source export.sh in esp-idf dir

Setup/Docker:

- mkdir -p $HOME/git ; git -C $HOME/git clone https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf.git
- export IDF_PATH=$HOME/git/esp-idf
- Build the docker image in $HOME/git/esp-idf/tools/docker with: docker build -t esp-idf .
- Prepend ./bin to PATH to use the cmake wrapper
- bin/cmake --build build --target menuconfig
   -> Set toolchain prefix to: xtensa-esp32-elf-
   -> Don't turn on C++ exception, that uses up too many sections in the image.
- idf-wrapper fullclean

Building code:
- bin/cmake --build build

Flash:
- bin/cmake --build flash

Monitor:
- bin/cmake --build monitor
